        Theme.MaterialComponents. However, doing so messes up some styles (e.g.
        the label of checkboxes will be too small, secondaryText on AppBar will
        be too large, and other issues). This proved to be hard to fix. For
        now, we derive from AppCompat theme, and use Theme.MaterialComponents
        as a separate theme for the material components.
    -->
